BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-73
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260318T035242
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260328T230000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260329T010000
SUMMARY:No Tyrants Rally
LOCATION:(métro Bonaventure)
DESCRIPTION:2026-03-28 23:00:00\n\n(métro Bonaventure)\n\nhttps://www.ope
 nstreetmap.org/relation/18917227\n\nAfter the powerful momentum of our pre
 vious gatherings\, Indivisible Québec is returning to the streets to defe
 nd democracy — together.\nOn March 28\, citizens from across Québec and
  beyond will gather at Place du Canada in downtown Montréal for the NO TY
 RANTS Rally — Defending Democracy Together\, part of a growing movement 
 of peaceful civic action standing up for democratic values\, human rights\
 , and the rule of law.\nWe are proud to welcome guest speakers including c
 onstitutional lawyer and political analyst Frédéric Bérard and author\,
  activist\, and former Member of Parliament Charlie Angus\, who will also 
 perform with his band The Grievous Angels.\nWhether you are a longtime adv
 ocate or simply someone who believes democracy is worth protecting\, your 
 presence matters.\nRSVP to attend:\nhttps://actionnetwork.org/events/montr
 eal-quebec-canada-no-tyrants-rally-30\nWant to help make the event possibl
 e? Join our amazing team of volunteers helping with outreach\, logistics\,
  and welcoming participants.\nJoin the Indivisible Québec volunteer team:
 \nhttps://actionnetwork.org/forms/join-the-iq-volunteer-team\nTogether we 
 stand for democracy.\nTogether we defend our institutions.\nThe power belo
 ngs to the people.\n✊ No to authoritarianism. No to autocracy. No Tyrant
 s.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/relation/18917227
END:VEVENT
