BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-78
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260318T035242
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260329T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260329T160000
SUMMARY:Queer Quilting Bee
LOCATION:1385 Ontario Est (métro Beaudry)
DESCRIPTION:2026-03-29 14:00:00\n\n1385 Ontario Est (métro Beaudry)\n\nht
 tps://www.openstreetmap.org/node/6018496602\n\nHow can textiles preserve h
 istory? What are the scraps of connection that make us who we are? This wo
 rkshop investigates piecework and appliqué as means of expression and con
 ceptual platform for 2SLGBTQIA+ expression. Starting with a scrap exchange
  of meaningful cloth\, participants will work with collective material as 
 a nod to the tradition of a quilting bee. We will focus on ‘crazy quilt
 ’ patchwork and ‘fancywork’ embroidery\, where participants can embe
 llish a small patchwork quilt block (12″ x 12″) with markers of their 
 identity and contemporary times\, such as names\, dates\, sites\, and souv
 enirs.\nMarch 29\, 2-5 pm\nLes Affûtés (Village)\, 1385 Ontario E.\nREGI
 STRATION REQUIRED (free &amp\; limited spots! See the full programme in ou
 r bio for sign up)\nAaron McIntosh is a cross-disciplinary artist and four
 th-generation quiltmaker whose work mines the intersections of material cu
 lture\, family tradition\, sexual desire and identity politics. His exhibi
 tion record includes numerous solo and group exhibitions\, most recently H
 ot House/Maison chaude at FOFA Gallery\, The Gloaming at Pierre-François 
 Ouellette art contemporain\, Entanglements at Northeastern University\, an
 d Radical Tradition: Quilts and Social Change at the Toledo Museum of Art.
  Since 2015\, McIntosh has managed Invasive Queer Kudzu\, a community stor
 ytelling and archive project across the 2SLGBTQ+ Southern United States.\n
 Part of Owning Our Histories: Celebrating DIY Archives from Queer &amp\; B
 IPOC MTL\n#communityarchives #queerquilting #owningourhistories
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/node/6018496602
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-79
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260318T035242
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260330T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260330T200000
SUMMARY:Permanence de l'Achoppe
LOCATION:1800 Letourneux (métro Pie-IX)
DESCRIPTION:2026-03-30 18:00:00\n\n1800 Letourneux (métro Pie-IX)\n\nhttp
 s://www.openstreetmap.org/way/363150208\n\nLes permanences de l’Achoppe 
 reprennent! Le centre social et sa bibliotheque vous acceuillent tous les 
 lundis de 6 à 9pm.\nVenez nous rencontrer\, boire un coup\, lire un zine 
 et plus encore! Nouveauté : on vous propose de venir imprimer des zines q
 ue vous voudriez lire (dans la mesure du raisonnable et si l’imprimante 
 coopere) sur donation volontaire.\n///\nL’Achoppe is having open hours a
 gain! Come meet us and hang out in the social center and its library on mo
 ndays\, from 6 to 9pm. New : you can print zines that you want to read (if
  the printer accepts and in reasonable amounts)\, PWYC\n///\nL’Achoppe t
 iene horas de apertura de nuevo! El centro social y su biblioteca te dan l
 a bienvenida los lunes de 18:00 a 21:00. ¡Ven a conocernos\, toma algo\, 
 lee un fanzine y mucho más! Nuevo: te ofrecemos venir a imprimir fanzines
  que quieras leer (dentro de lo razonable y si la imprenta colabora) media
 nte una donación voluntaria.\n&nbsp\;
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/way/363150208
END:VEVENT
